<subSubSection pageId="113" pageNumber="114" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="113.[151,1437,618,1615]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1338,1363]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[658,843,1338,1363]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchripennis">
<emphasis box="[658,843,1338,1363]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">A. pulchripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the body with golden-green reflection; the clypeus short, with the apical margin truncate, and the clypeal carina distinct from the clypeus; the antennal scrobe carinate; the ocelli very small; the transverse pronotal carina present; the posterior margin with a posterior pronotal sulcus; the notaulus narrow; the metapostnotum without longitudinal ridges; and the mesopleural suture opened, whereas 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[250,436,1482,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchripennis">
<emphasis box="[250,436,1482,1507]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">A. pulchripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the body black; the clypeus very short, with the apical margin angulate, and clypeal carina hardly distinct from the clypeus; the antennal scrobe ecarinate; the ocelli small; the posterior margin without a posterior pronotal sulcus; the transverse pronotal carina absent; the notaulus very narrow; the metapostnotum without longitudinal ridges; and the mesopleural suture closed.
</paragraph>
